  "prompt": "Can I flash SuperSU from stock recovery in Android?",
  "response": "Flashing SuperSU (or any custom recovery) from a stock recovery on Android is generally not possible in the traditional sense, as stock recovery usually does not support flashing custom ZIP files. Stock recovery is designed primarily for performing factory resets, applying official OTA updates, and accessing other system-level recovery options.\n\nHere are some key points regarding flashing SuperSU:\n\n1. **Custom Recovery Required**: To flash SuperSU, you typically need a custom recovery like TWRP or ClockworkMod Recovery. These custom recoveries support ZIP file installations and provide additional functionalities not available in stock recovery.\n\n2. **Rooting Process**: If you want to root your device using SuperSU, you would generally follow these steps:\n   - Unlock the bootloader of your device.\n   - Install a custom recovery (like TWRP).\n   - Boot into the custom recovery.\n   - Flash the SuperSU ZIP file from your device's storage.\n\n3. **Backup**: Always ensure you back up your important data before attempting to flash any files, as rooting and modifying system partitions can lead to data loss or bricking your device.\n\n4. **Model-Specific Instructions**: The steps for unlocking the bootloader and installing a custom recovery can vary between Android devices. Always refer to specific guides for your device model.\n\n5. **Risk**: Remember that rooting your device and flashing custom software can void your warranty and may expose your device to security vulnerabilities.\n\nIf you're determined to root your device and flash SuperSU, make sure to follow a reliable guide tailored to your specific Android device model.",
